WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.800 --> 00:00:05.274
Checking an entry means understanding whether the right document supports it.

2
00:00:07.548 --> 00:00:13.482
Vera starts from the sampled journal row and looks first across FatturaPA XML and

3
00:00:13.482 --> 00:00:14.874
authorized exports.

4
00:00:17.147 --> 00:00:18.893
It compares amount, date,

5
00:00:18.893 --> 00:00:23.573
document number and counterparty while keeping each source visible.

6
00:00:25.846 --> 00:00:28.686
Strong matches move into the supported set.

7
00:00:28.686 --> 00:00:31.789
Ambiguous cases remain in the review queue with

8
00:00:31.789 --> 00:00:34.958
the reason and the specific document to inspect.

9
00:00:37.232 --> 00:00:42.248
The result is a workpaper that links every checked entry to its evidence and keeps

10
00:00:42.248 --> 00:00:43.471
exceptions separate.

11
00:00:45.745 --> 00:00:49.200
From a sampled row to support the reviewer can follow.
